<title>USA: GM asked to pay $50mln-$75mln in crash suit.</title>
<headline>GM asked to pay $50mln-$75mln in crash suit.</headline>
<dateline>JACKSONVILLE, Fla 1997-01-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>An attorney for a woman who suffered severe brain damage in the crash of a Chevrolet Astro van asked a jury Wednesday to order General Motors to pay $50 million-$75 million in punitive damages.</p>
<p>In opening arguments in the punitive damages phase of the product liability trial, Chris Searcy, representing plaintiff Therese Hunter, described such an award as &quot;extremely conservative and reasonable under the circumstances.&quot;</p>
